reviews.review:
Greatest movie ever!
Edge of your seat the entire time!
Jaw dropping. 

Much like how the Force Awakens was similar to New Hope, this one also follows in the footsteps of Return of the Jedi. 
However, it throws in many twists and turns.

It does pay homage and tribute to the previous films with easter eggs galore! 

Definitely will see again and again and again in theaters!
well made,  visually stunning but too much crammed into this last of the saga.
A great way to close the Saga!
While entertaining ROS light speed skipped through both plot and characters making ROS feel disjointed as they jumped from one system to another in an inconceivably quick time.
A return to the swashbuckling fun JJ Abrams first introduced in The Force Awakens, though the first 30 minutes crams nearly a movie's worth plot and character.
Best of the new trilogy.   My two sons (10-14) agreed.    Very good way to end the series, but left an opening for another????
Not a great movie, but it hit all the fanboy moments.
It's maybe the worst Star Wars in 42 years. The movie is really boring with nothing surprising, no connection with the characters. Such a pity after a great episode VIII.
I enjoyed seeing the collection of old and new characters, and overall entertaining, but it started a little slow for a Star Wars episode.

I actually enjoyed this movie - and more than I expected... it may be the best of the sequel trilogy. It tries to fix some of the holes of the "Last Jedi". That was the only movie I watched twice in the cinema but the more I think about it the more sad or enraged I become with it... It's certainly not perfect and it will probably open new holes in the Star Wars mythology. Very good performances, Rey and Kylio/Ben well developed. Surprisingly, I liked the  Reylo Bit and ended up thinking that Ben should have been let to live. 

Eventually, once new people take over, reflection comes and everyone sees things in perspective, I would sincerely hope there will be another trilogy or something taking the story further... but for now, Lucasfilm has messed up things  so much that ...
